Netsh trace - This is usually a good starting point for NTLM authentication cases to first understand the error and even the timestamp to correlate with other logs. Please be sure to know what endpoint we are trying to reach to understand which (if multiple) authentication error is of interest.
Use the commands below in an Administrator Command prompt to capture the tracing. You should start the tracing, reproduce the issue, then stop the tracing.
Depending on the product type, use one of the commands below to start a network trace.
Windows edition	Suggested command
Windows client	netsh trace start InternetClient persistent=yes traceFile=%temp%%computername%_Netmon.etl capture=yes maxsize=1024
Windows Server - Member Server only	netsh trace start persistent=yes traceFile=%temp%%computername%_Netmon.etl capture=yes maxsize=1024
Windows Server - Domain controller	netsh trace start persistent=yes traceFile=%temp%%computername%_Netmon.etl capture=yes maxsize=1024




