A. DNS configuration (this is critical)
Clients must use AD‑integrated DNS, not public or static DNS pointing only to Region A.
Check:
	• Client DNS servers include DCs from Region A and Region B
No public DNS (8.8.8.8, 1.1.1.1) listed
2. How to check SRV records (two supported ways)
✅ Method 1: From a CLIENT or SERVER (most common & recommended)
This checks exactly what the client sees, which is what matters.
A. Check “all DCs in the domain” (cross‑site visibility)
Run this from the client (or any domain member):

NSLOOKUP DC1.CONTOSO.COM 
nltest /sc_verify:contoso.com
Nltest /sc_reset:contoso.com\DC01.contoso.com
Klist purge
Ipconfig /flushdns
BAT
nslookup
set type=SRV
_ldap._tcp.dc._msdcs.contoso.com
``
Show more lines
✅ Expected result:
	• Multiple SRV records
	• One entry per DC (Region A + Region B)
